-----------------------------------------------------------------------
ABOUT
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
BabelGraph is written by Gary Weissman, 2008.

BabelGraph 0.2 is open source software, released under the GPLv3 License (see attached for the license itself)

For more information visit http://www.babelgraph.org/ or contact gary@babelgraph.org

BabelGraph is a graph analysis and visualization program helpful for investigations of graphs and social networks.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
INSTALL
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
WINDOWS:
1. Open the zip file by double-clicking or using WinZip.

2. Double Click on BabelGraph.exe and the program will run

MAC:
1. Mount the disk image by double clicking on the .dmg file

2. Double click on BabelGraph to launch the program


LINUX:
NB. To build BabelGraph you will need Qt 4.4 installed on your computer.  You can download it from trolltech.com

1. gunzip BabelGraph-x.x.tar.gz
2. tar -xvf BabelGraph-x.x.tar
3. cd BabelGraph-x.x
4. qmake-qt4
5. make
6. ./BabelGraph


